01:55:32.000 --> 01:55:34.870
kept growing in the lights. And I

01:55:34.880 --> 01:55:36.550
thought that was kind of neat. I don't

01:55:36.560 --> 01:55:40.470
know what that meant, but I saw it. So,

01:55:40.480 --> 01:55:43.030
what else did I see in the last

01:55:43.040 --> 01:55:47.669
video? Oh, I saw John Hagee's church.

01:55:47.679 --> 01:55:51.910
Yeah, I saw John Hagee and I saw a place

01:55:51.920 --> 01:55:53.750
of revival.

01:55:53.760 --> 01:55:58.390
John Hagee Cornerstone Church had

01:55:58.400 --> 01:56:01.350
some kind of new somebody. I don't know

01:56:01.360 --> 01:56:04.550
who it was, but they had a golden coat

01:56:04.560 --> 01:56:07.910
on. They had a golden

01:56:07.920 --> 01:56:12.470
suit that was shiny and metallic.

01:56:12.480 --> 01:56:15.830
It had a paisley print,

01:56:15.840 --> 01:56:18.870
beautiful like that kind of calligraphy,

01:56:18.880 --> 01:56:20.310
like whenever you see that

01:56:20.320 --> 01:56:23.589
kind of artistry on a suit.

01:56:23.589 --> 01:56:23.599
It

01:56:23.599 --> 01:56:28.950
was a light, faded-out gray, like

01:56:28.960 --> 01:56:32.950
silver on top of gold.

01:56:32.960 --> 01:56:36.870
So the gold jacket the man

01:56:36.870 --> 01:56:36.880
had—whoever

01:56:36.880 --> 01:56:39.830
this was—he had a white shirt with

01:56:39.840 --> 01:56:43.589
a tie, and a golden jacket that was

01:56:43.599 --> 01:56:46.709
metallic and shone like gold.

01:56:46.719 --> 01:56:49.750
That's how shiny it was. It had

01:56:49.760 --> 01:56:54.950
an overlay with a light

01:56:54.960 --> 01:56:58.709
silver pinstripe design that

01:56:58.719 --> 01:57:00.950
looked like a coat of many

01:57:00.960 --> 01:57:03.109
colors, but silver and gold. It

01:57:03.109 --> 01:57:03.119
was beautifully

01:57:03.119 --> 01:57:06.550
designed all

01:57:06.560 --> 01:57:08.950
over the sleeves with embroidery—that's a

01:57:08.960 --> 01:57:11.030
better way to say it, maybe. But that's the

01:57:11.040 --> 01:57:14.149
way the coat was. And then I saw Joel

01:57:14.149 --> 01:57:14.159
Osteen's

01:57:14.159 --> 01:57:17.109
church. Many people

01:57:17.119 --> 01:57:18.870
have discredited him and said, "Well,

01:57:18.880 --> 01:57:20.310
he's not radical enough. He's done all

01:57:20.320 --> 01:57:22.709
these things."And I'm just telling you

01:57:22.719 --> 01:57:25.270
what I saw, okay? But the Lord said,

01:57:25.280 --> 01:57:29.030
"I'm going to use this place as a

01:57:29.040 --> 01:57:32.870
place for people to gather

01:57:32.880 --> 01:57:36.550
for the major harvest."All these major

01:57:36.560 --> 01:57:38.070
sanctuaries

01:57:38.080 --> 01:57:41.510
were full of people gathered for the

01:57:41.510 --> 01:57:41.520
end-time

01:57:41.520 --> 01:57:44.950
outpouring—Lakewood,

01:57:44.950 --> 01:57:44.960
Cornerstone—and

01:57:44.960 --> 01:57:47.669
these

01:57:47.669 --> 01:57:47.679
were

01:57:47.679 --> 01:57:50.629
churches in Texas. As I was looking

01:57:50.639 --> 01:57:52.629
across, the Lord said, "Each one of

01:57:52.639 --> 01:57:55.350
these places, Brandon,"he said,

01:57:55.360 --> 01:57:57.030
"each one of these places will be

01:57:57.040 --> 01:58:01.350
full of

01:58:01.350 --> 01:58:01.360
people."So

01:58:01.360 --> 01:58:04.870
I don't get into, "Well,

01:58:04.880 --> 01:58:06.390
this one's this."No, I'm talking

01:58:06.400 --> 01:58:09.189
about the body of Christ working

01:58:09.199 --> 01:58:11.669
together, regardless of whether you like the way

01:58:11.679 --> 01:58:13.270
somebody preaches or if they're not radical

01:58:13.280 --> 01:58:16.149
enough for you.

01:58:16.149 --> 01:58:16.159
I

01:58:16.159 --> 01:58:17.990
get all kinds of

01:58:18.000 --> 01:58:20.870
emails, but listen, I love

01:58:20.880 --> 01:58:22.790
everybody and I pray for everybody,

01:58:22.800 --> 01:58:25.030
regardless of how radical they are, or

01:58:25.040 --> 01:58:27.109
how on fire you think they should be, or if

01:58:27.109 --> 01:58:27.119
they are

01:58:27.119 --> 01:58:29.430
too in the world,

01:58:29.440 --> 01:58:31.430
or whatever. I'm talking about

01:58:31.430 --> 01:58:31.440
praying

01:58:31.440 --> 01:58:34.310
for revival in everybody's hearts,

01:58:34.320 --> 01:58:36.229
that we're all here for a

01:58:36.239 --> 01:58:38.390
purpose and we're here right now, and God

01:58:38.390 --> 01:58:38.400
is

01:58:38.400 --> 01:58:39.910
going to use every single one of

01:58:39.920 --> 01:58:43.990
us if we just say yes.

01:58:44.000 --> 01:58:47.030
It's time to get excited and say, "Jesus

01:58:47.040 --> 01:58:48.950
Christ is coming,"and not have petty

01:58:48.960 --> 01:58:51.510
differences and say, "Yeah, you know what,

01:58:51.510 --> 01:58:51.520
they

01:58:51.520 --> 01:58:53.189
should be a little bit bolder about

01:58:53.199 --> 01:58:55.189
what they believe and be more

01:58:55.189 --> 01:58:55.199
radical."It's

01:58:55.199 --> 01:58:57.189
all hands on deck

01:58:57.199 --> 01:58:58.870
right now, and He's going to use the

01:58:58.870 --> 01:58:58.880
Methodists,

01:58:58.880 --> 01:59:00.550
He's going to use the

01:59:00.560 --> 01:59:02.149
Church of Christ, He's going to use

01:59:02.159 --> 01:59:06.070
whoever will say, "I'm hungry and I

01:59:06.080 --> 01:59:07.669
want to be a part of this

01:59:07.669 --> 01:59:07.679
end-time

01:59:07.679 --> 01:59:09.990
harvest because the harvest is

01:59:10.000 --> 01:59:12.709
plentiful by the billions and the

01:59:12.709 --> 01:59:12.719
laborers

01:59:12.719 --> 01:59:17.589
are

01:59:17.589 --> 01:59:17.599
few."So

01:59:17.599 --> 01:59:20.790
I saw that across the land. I

01:59:20.800 --> 01:59:23.109
saw many people being used, I saw many

01:59:23.119 --> 01:59:26.550
churches, and then I saw elders.

01:59:26.560 --> 01:59:29.510
He said, "Pray for John,

01:59:29.520 --> 01:59:33.990
for his heart,

01:59:33.990 --> 01:59:34.000
Hagee's

01:59:34.000 --> 01:59:38.950
heart, for him to

01:59:38.960 --> 01:59:41.350
live long and finish

01:59:41.350 --> 01:59:41.360
strong."I

01:59:41.360 --> 01:59:45.510
saw to pray for his health,

01:59:45.520 --> 01:59:48.470
concerning his health, to pray for this

01:59:48.480 --> 01:59:50.070
man's health. I didn't realize he

01:59:50.080 --> 01:59:53.669
was 85 years old, but I saw to pray for

01:59:53.679 --> 01:59:55.350
his health. And I saw him standing in a

01:59:55.360 --> 01:59:57.430
line next to another man. I'm not

01:59:57.440 --> 01:59:58.550
even going to say his name—it doesn't

01:59:58.550 --> 01:59:58.560
matter—but

01:59:58.560 --> 02:00:01.430
I saw these two men, and I

02:00:01.440 --> 02:00:04.470
saw other men coming beside

02:00:04.470 --> 02:00:04.480
them.

02:00:04.480 --> 02:00:09.589
There were a lot of elders;

02:00:09.599 --> 02:00:11.109
that's all the Lord allowed me to

02:00:11.119 --> 02:00:14.070
say. They were standing there

02:00:14.080 --> 02:00:17.030
and the Lord said, "Pray for these men. I

02:00:17.030 --> 02:00:17.040
told you

02:00:17.040 --> 02:00:20.070
there

02:00:20.070 --> 02:00:20.080
will

02:00:20.080 --> 02:00:21.990
be a changing of the

02:00:22.000 --> 02:00:23.669
guard concerning certain people, and

02:00:23.679 --> 02:00:26.229
they'll go home, but there are certain

02:00:26.239 --> 02:00:28.709
people who have had a voice, who

02:00:28.709 --> 02:00:28.719
have

02:00:28.719 --> 02:00:31.109
had a great revelation of the Word,

02:00:31.109 --> 02:00:31.119
and

02:00:31.119 --> 02:00:34.870
we need them to stick around

02:00:34.880 --> 02:00:37.910
because you need elders to help these

02:00:37.920 --> 02:00:40.629
young ones out."You learn from your

02:00:40.639 --> 02:00:42.470
elders.

02:00:42.480 --> 02:00:44.310
You learn from these fathers of the

02:00:44.320 --> 02:00:48.070
faith who have been here for decades,

02:00:48.070 --> 02:00:48.080
who

02:00:48.080 --> 02:00:50.709
have lived it and experienced it.

02:00:50.719 --> 02:00:52.229
That's why I pray for Billy Burke; I

02:00:52.239 --> 02:00:53.910
pray for these people.

02:00:53.920 --> 02:00:55.830
They're in their 70s and some of them in

02:00:55.840 --> 02:00:58.070
their 80s, and we need them to stick

02:00:58.080 --> 02:01:00.870
around.

02:01:02.400 --> 02:01:04.950
They may have a background position,

02:01:04.960 --> 02:01:06.790
instructing from the sidelines like a

02:01:06.800 --> 02:01:09.030
coach while the other young guys are

02:01:09.040 --> 02:01:11.750
playing the game, but you've got to

02:01:11.760 --> 02:01:13.990
have a coach who has some knowledge so

02:01:14.000 --> 02:01:16.870
you win. You have some Holy Ghost

02:01:16.880 --> 02:01:19.189
knowledge over here. When you live

02:01:19.199 --> 02:01:21.430
something, you can say something. A

02:01:21.440 --> 02:01:23.350
lot of these young bucks

02:01:23.360 --> 02:01:24.629
don't know anything; they're

02:01:24.639 --> 02:01:26.550
just starting out like me. That's why

02:01:26.560 --> 02:01:28.070
I'm always gleaning. I'm asking

02:01:28.080 --> 02:01:31.350
these elders, "Please show

02:01:31.350 --> 02:01:31.360
me."Humble

02:01:31.360 --> 02:01:34.070
yourself to the elders and say, "Listen,

02:01:34.080 --> 02:01:35.589
help me. I don't have everything all

02:01:35.599 --> 02:01:37.109
figured out.

02:01:39.440 --> 02:01:41.270
You may have been through the '70s, '80s, '90s,

02:01:41.280 --> 02:01:43.830
and the early 2000s,

02:01:43.840 --> 02:01:46.149
and you've got some wisdom in you

02:01:46.149 --> 02:01:46.159
that I need."I

02:01:46.159 --> 02:01:49.270
pray for the

02:01:49.280 --> 02:01:51.589
elders to have a soft heart toward the

02:01:51.599 --> 02:01:53.750
young people and say, "Listen, you can glean

02:01:53.750 --> 02:01:53.760
it."It's

02:01:53.760 --> 02:01:55.510
their time of

02:01:55.520 --> 02:01:57.350
impartation—that

02:01:57.360 --> 02:01:59.430
is what

02:01:59.440 --> 02:02:00.870
I'm saying. But there will be a lot of

02:02:00.880 --> 02:02:02.870
them, I've seen, because of their health

02:02:02.880 --> 02:02:05.109
and certain issues, that the enemy would

02:02:05.119 --> 02:02:07.910
want them to go home early,

02:02:07.920 --> 02:02:11.830
and we don't want them going home.

02:02:11.840 --> 02:02:14.629
That's just what

02:02:14.639 --> 02:02:17.350
I see, and so I pray for

02:02:17.360 --> 02:02:20.310
these older generals. We pray for

02:02:20.320 --> 02:02:22.550
their hearts, we pray for their bodies.

02:02:22.560 --> 02:02:25.669
John Kilpatrick and these elders,

02:02:25.679 --> 02:02:28.310
pray for their health

02:02:28.320 --> 02:02:29.910
because the Lord told me John

02:02:29.920 --> 02:02:31.830
Kilpatrick would be a major voice in the

02:02:31.840 --> 02:02:34.310
end times—leaders

02:02:34.310 --> 02:02:34.320
who

02:02:34.320 --> 02:02:37.910
are

02:02:37.920 --> 02:02:39.990
not flaky in their doctrine, where you

02:02:40.000 --> 02:02:42.390
have some people with some backbone

02:02:42.390 --> 02:02:42.400
who

02:02:42.400 --> 02:02:44.229
stand for something that's good, like it

02:02:44.239 --> 02:02:47.510
was back in the revival of

02:02:47.520 --> 02:02:49.589
Brownsville. They've been through

02:02:49.599 --> 02:02:52.470
it; they lived it. They may not have

02:02:52.480 --> 02:02:54.390
done everything always right, but who

02:02:54.400 --> 02:02:56.070
has?

02:02:58.480 --> 02:03:00.550
Nobody. I don't know anybody. But

02:03:00.560 --> 02:03:02.390
at least you can learn something

02:03:02.400 --> 02:03:04.149
from their good things and their bad

02:03:04.159 --> 02:03:06.070
stuff and say, "Listen, there's

02:03:06.080 --> 02:03:07.510
something there."That's why Oral Roberts

02:03:07.520 --> 02:03:10.790
was a diamond. Look at what he

02:03:10.800 --> 02:03:12.790
did. He was a pioneer of the healing

02:03:12.800 --> 02:03:15.189
revival, went throughout the whole world,

02:03:15.199 --> 02:03:17.589
and nobody had really done it before him

02:03:17.599 --> 02:03:19.910
in this generation. He was a pioneer.

02:03:19.920 --> 02:03:21.270
And there were certain people who had

02:03:21.280 --> 02:03:23.270
the opportunity to sit with him and

02:03:23.280 --> 02:03:25.109
break bread with him, who got a glimpse

02:03:25.119 --> 02:03:26.870
of something and learned something from

02:03:26.880 --> 02:03:28.229
him. That's why I said "The Ultimate Voice"by

02:03:28.229 --> 02:03:28.239
Oral

02:03:28.239 --> 02:03:31.030
Roberts will change your

02:03:31.040 --> 02:03:33.109
life. It's one of, I think, the last

02:03:33.109 --> 02:03:33.119
books

02:03:33.119 --> 02:03:35.750
he ever wrote. And I told Diana, she

02:03:35.760 --> 02:03:39.030
reads it to me every year. Every year we

02:03:39.040 --> 02:03:41.510
read "The Ultimate Voice"by Oral Roberts,

02:03:41.520 --> 02:03:44.390
and without fail, we always read

02:03:44.390 --> 02:03:44.400
Oral

02:03:44.400 --> 02:03:46.149
Roberts at the beginning of the year.

02:03:46.159 --> 02:03:48.870
Read that book, and read it again and

02:03:48.880 --> 02:03:51.510
again, because of the

02:03:51.520 --> 02:03:53.430
wisdom that comes out of that book, it

02:03:53.440 --> 02:03:56.709
will change your life.

02:03:56.719 --> 02:03:59.510
We get books all the time from

02:03:59.520 --> 02:04:01.030
people and you go, "What life

02:04:01.040 --> 02:04:03.669
experiences do you have to write a

02:04:03.669 --> 02:04:03.679
book?"Not

02:04:03.679 --> 02:04:06.390
trying to dog your

02:04:06.400 --> 02:04:08.229
circumstance, but I like to read the

02:04:08.239 --> 02:04:09.910
books of somebody who has been through

02:04:09.920 --> 02:04:11.589
something

02:04:11.599 --> 02:04:13.589
and come out—going through the valley of

02:04:13.599 --> 02:04:15.589
the shadow of death and

02:04:15.599 --> 02:04:17.910
they didn't stay there.

02:04:17.920 --> 02:04:20.070
They may smell like a little smoke, but

02:04:20.080 --> 02:04:23.589
they have a testimony to tell about it.

02:04:23.599 --> 02:04:25.270
Give me some! Don't just write a book

02:04:25.270 --> 02:04:25.280
to

02:04:25.280 --> 02:04:27.589
write a book. You know, there's a lot of

02:04:27.599 --> 02:04:30.709
people writing books.

02:04:30.719 --> 02:04:32.790
I want something that has some oomph to

02:04:32.800 --> 02:04:35.589
it, where you have something that

02:04:35.599 --> 02:04:38.470
you imparted. You walked

02:04:38.480 --> 02:04:40.950
through some hell

02:04:40.960 --> 02:04:43.189
and you got on the other side of it, and

02:04:43.199 --> 02:04:45.830
it changed you because you didn't park

02:04:45.840 --> 02:04:48.310
your tent there and have

02:04:48.310 --> 02:04:48.320
a woe-is-me

02:04:48.320 --> 02:04:51.430
mentality. I get tired of that; I don't

02:04:51.440 --> 02:04:53.750
want to hear it.

02:04:53.760 --> 02:04:55.669
It's like people who are snot-nosed,

02:04:55.679 --> 02:04:58.229
like, "Shut up and sit down."Let's hear

02:04:58.239 --> 02:04:59.350
somebody who's been through something,

02:04:59.350 --> 02:04:59.360
who's

02:04:59.360 --> 02:05:01.510
come out not smelling, and

02:05:01.510 --> 02:05:01.520
has

02:05:01.520 --> 02:05:04.550
some integrity up in here.

02:05:04.560 --> 02:05:05.910
They don't have a scandal in their

02:05:05.920 --> 02:05:09.189
ministry where you walk away going, "That's

02:05:09.199 --> 02:05:11.109
so

02:05:11.109 --> 02:05:11.119
disappointing."Don't

02:05:11.119 --> 02:05:12.790
you get disappointed with that

02:05:12.800 --> 02:05:16.390
stuff? I know people have stuff

02:05:16.400 --> 02:05:18.629
they go through, but folks,

02:05:18.639 --> 02:05:20.629
I just want to glean from somebody

02:05:20.639 --> 02:05:24.470
who's been in ministry like Oral Roberts

02:05:24.480 --> 02:05:27.510
for 60-plus years or whatever it

02:05:27.520 --> 02:05:30.310
was, and is still standing strong on

02:05:30.320 --> 02:05:32.870
his deathbed and going home,

02:05:32.880 --> 02:05:35.030
and you go, "Wow."Or Kenneth

02:05:35.030 --> 02:05:35.040
Hagin.

02:05:35.040 --> 02:05:36.629
That's why we listen to

02:05:36.629 --> 02:05:36.639
Hagin

02:05:36.639 --> 02:05:40.709
all day today. Brother

02:05:40.709 --> 02:05:40.719
Hagin,

02:05:40.719 --> 02:05:43.189
we listen to Brother Hagin more than

02:05:43.199 --> 02:05:45.430
anything. And Kathryn Kuhlman, we

02:05:45.440 --> 02:05:47.510
listen and listen and listen to it.

02:05:47.520 --> 02:05:48.950
And you go, 'I've

02:05:48.950 --> 02:05:48.960
already...'Paisley

02:05:48.960 --> 02:05:50.790
goes, 'Daddy, I'm memorizing

02:05:50.790 --> 02:05:50.800
this.'I

02:05:50.800 --> 02:05:52.709
said, 'Yes, that's when it gets

02:05:52.719 --> 02:05:56.149
down inside of

02:05:56.149 --> 02:05:56.159
you.''I

02:05:56.159 --> 02:05:58.709
know this, Dad.'Yeah. That's when it

02:05:58.719 --> 02:06:00.709
changes you.

02:06:00.719 --> 02:06:02.470
You don't just hear it. Faith cometh by

02:06:02.480 --> 02:06:04.310
hearing and hearing and hearing and

02:06:04.320 --> 02:06:06.470
hearing. That's when it changes you.

02:06:06.480 --> 02:06:08.070
When it changes you from the inside out

02:06:08.080 --> 02:06:11.030
is how many times you've heard it over

02:06:11.040 --> 02:06:13.270
and over and over again. And I listen,

02:06:13.280 --> 02:06:14.390
Brother Hagin, I'm telling you, I've

02:06:14.400 --> 02:06:15.510
listened to some of his sermons

02:06:15.520 --> 02:06:18.390
probably, no exaggeration, 30 or 40 times.

02:06:18.400 --> 02:06:21.990
You go,

02:06:22.000 --> 02:06:23.270
'I know what he's going to say before he

02:06:23.280 --> 02:06:25.350
says it,'but that's when it gets you.

02:06:25.360 --> 02:06:27.270
It's going to change you. So, I don't

02:06:27.280 --> 02:06:31.189
know, hopefully that helps y'all.

02:06:31.189 --> 02:06:31.199
Do

02:06:31.199 --> 02:06:32.390
they have anything else?

02:06:32.400 --> 02:06:33.830
They're asking if you saw any more

02:06:33.840 --> 02:06:36.310
things about the volcano.

02:06:36.320 --> 02:06:37.589
I haven't seen any more about

02:06:37.599 --> 02:06:39.350
the volcano. In fact, I asked the Father

02:06:39.360 --> 02:06:41.430
about the volcanoes. I said, 'Lord, you

